---
title: Cheddar & Apple Grilled Cheese Sandos with Cranberry-Dijon Jam
description: Sure, a classic white bread and American grilled cheese hits the spot every now and then, but try one bite of this 15-minute sweet and savory lunch idea, and you may never quite be satisfied with the old standby again. Sourdough slices are swiped with sweet and tangy cranberry-Dijon jam, then layered with cheddar and mild Monterey Jack cheeses and crisp apple slices. They’re griddled in butter until perfectly golden brown and melty. Flip onto your plate, and boom—lunch, elevated!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/64a4fab73223226bfd2b8b2b-a589e79e.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/64a4fab73223226bfd2b8b2b.pdf
author: Sara Heilman
servings: 2
time required: 15 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 520 kcal
  fat: 25 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 71 g
  sugar: 16 g
  protein: 16 g
  fiber: 2 g
  sodium: 940 mg
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/cheddar-and-apple-grilled-cheese-sandos-64a4fab73223226bfd2b8b2b
cuisine: North America
---

Wash and dry produce.

Halve, core, and thinly slice half the @Apple{1} (all for 4 servings).

In a #small bowl{}, stir together @Dijon Mustard{2%teaspoon} and @Cranberry Jam{1}.

  Lay @Sourdough Bread{4%slice} out on a clean work surface. Spread half the bread
slices with cranberry-Dijon jam. Layer with @Cheddar Cheese{1/2%cup} and as
many apple slices as you like. Top with @Monterey Jack Cheese{1/4%cup} and
remaining bread slices.

Heat a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%teaspoon} in a large, preferably
nonstick, pan over medium heat. Add sandwiches. Cook until bread is golden
brown and cheese melts, ~{3-4%minutes} per side.

> TIP: You may need to work in batches, adding another drizzle of oil for each batch.

Cut grilled cheese sandos in half on a diagonal and divide between plates. Serve
with any remaining apple slices.